President Obama expresses his condolences to the families of Eyal Yifrach, Gilad Shaar, and Naftali Fraenkel, who were killed in a senseless act of terror. He condemns the attack and offers full support to Israel and the Palestinian Authority in finding the perpetrators and bringing them to justice. He urges all parties to avoid actions that could worsen the situation and assures Israel of the full support and friendship of the United States.